The paper focuses on the role of software architecture in Continuous Delivery and Deployment (CD), which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also discusses the design of operations-friendly architectures, which relates to the software design and development (cs.SD) sub-category. Additionally, the paper touches on the deployment of software systems, which falls under the distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of small and independent deployment units, which relates to programming languages (cs.PL) and cybernetics (cs.CY) sub-categories.
